sentances: She was a talented singer, and after graduating high school in [Aurora] she enrolled at Denver Community College to study music.
translation: Dheweke dadi penyanyi sing bakat, lan sawise lulus SMA ing [Aurora] dheweke mlebu ing Denver Community College kanggo sinau musik.

sentances: [Aurora] Snow canvassed the adult industry to see which television shows excite its XXX talent.
translation: [Aurora] Salju ngawasi industri diwasa kanggo ndeleng acara televisi sing nyenengake bakat XXX.

sentances: How did it come to be then that she would feel an affinity for [Aurora] and start to care for her?
translation: Kepiye carane dheweke bakal ngrasakake afinitas karo [Aurora] lan wiwit ngrawat dheweke?

sentances: Clevenger sounds little better than he did 10 years ago in a letter to the editor in the [Aurora] Advertiser.
translation: Clevenger muni luwih apik tinimbang 10 taun kepungkur ing surat menyang editor ing [Aurora] Pengiklan.

sentances: Editor's Note: An earlier version of this article said Miller was from Marrionville but he lived in neighboring [Aurora].
translation: Cathetan Editor: Versi sadurungé saka artikel iki ngandika Miller saka Marrionville nanging dheweke manggon ing tetanggan [Aurora].

sentances: The moon seemed to smile on him; the [Aurora] appeared to dance with unwonted vigour, as if in glee; the very stars winked at him!
translation: Rembulan katon mesem marang dheweke; [Aurora] katon nari kanthi semangat sing ora biasa, kaya-kaya bungah; lintang banget nglirik dheweke!

sentances: The storm, however, was over; the moon and stars were shining in a clear sky, and the [Aurora] was dancing merrily.
translation: Badai, Nanging, wis liwat; rembulan lan lintang padha sumunar ing langit kang padhang, lan [Aurora] njoget riang.

sentances: Thus also Mary, the spiritual [Aurora], had to be conceived and born before the appearance of the Sun of Justice in this world.
translation: Mangkono uga Maria, [Aurora] spiritual, kudu dikandung lan lair sadurunge katon Srengenge Kehakiman ing jagad iki.

sentances: Trying to fathom the abyss below them, he saw the flames of the [Aurora] borealis reflected in the water of an immense lake.
translation: Nyoba ngerteni jurang ing ngisor dheweke, dheweke weruh geni saka [Aurora] borealis sing katon ing banyu tlaga sing gedhe banget.

sentances: It is impossible to describe here the various experiences and doings of [Aurora].
translation: Ora bisa digambarake ing kene macem-macem pengalaman lan tumindak [Aurora].

sentances: The [Chatoyant] eyes of the leopard stared back, a flicker of restlessness in their brilliant yellow deeps.
translation: Mripat macan tutul [Chatoyant] mandeng mburi, kelip-kelip gelisah ing jerone kuning sing padhang.

sentances: Cymophane, or [Chatoyant] chrysoberyl, may also be asteriated.
translation: Cymophane, utawa [Chatoyant] chrysoberyl, bisa uga asterasi.

sentances: She invariably wore gloves out of doors and a veil to conceal the [Chatoyant] eyes.
translation: Dheweke tansah nganggo sarung tangan metu saka lawang lan kudung kanggo ndhelikake mata [Chatoyant].

sentances: There was a river there too; not a little bolt of [Chatoyant] silk like the Avon, which they would have called a "crick" back there.
translation: Ing kono uga ana kali; ora bolt sethitik saka [Chatoyant] sutra kaya Avon, kang padha bakal disebut "crick" bali ana.

sentances: His reviews, rightly, call him “sweet,” “[Demure],”  “easygoing.”
translation: Ulasan dheweke, kanthi bener, nyebut dheweke "manis," "[Demure],"  "gampang".

sentances: The cover was relatively [Demure] given more recent issues and seemed to signal a turning point for the softcore sex magazine.
translation: Sampul kasebut relatif [Demure] diwenehi masalah sing luwih anyar lan katon minangka tandha titik balik kanggo majalah seks softcore.

sentances: Kate wore one of her trusty stand-bys, a full-length LK Bennet coat, in red, natch, and [Demure] black heels.
translation: Kate nganggo salah sijine stand-by sing dipercaya, jas LK Bennet lengkap, nganggo sepatu hak ireng abang, natch, lan [Demure].

sentances: Trim and [Demure], she is, for one thing, seemingly an eighth of his size.
translation: Trim lan [Demure], dheweke, siji-sijine, kayane ukurane kaping wolu.

sentances: Chris was brilliant, deferential, even [Demure], full of conviction.
translation: Chris sarwa, deferential, malah [Demure], kebak bebendhu.

sentances: On the other hand, Vera Galloway was transformed into a [Demure]-looking shop assistant waiting a customers' orders.
translation: Ing tangan liyane, Vera Galloway iki rubah menyang [Demure]-looking asisten toko nunggu pesenan pelanggan.

sentances: What scenes, what tragedies, what comedies, those bright houses and [Demure] little villas concealed.
translation: Pemandangan apa, tragedi apa, komedi apa, omah-omah sing padhang lan vila-vila cilik [Demure] sing didhelikake.

sentances: You never saw a more [Demure], harmless and even helpless looking bit of a thing in your life.
translation: Sampeyan ora tau weruh sing luwih [Demure], ora mbebayani lan malah ora duwe daya ing urip sampeyan.

sentances: Father Letheby, at the end of the table, looked as [Demure] as a nun.
translation: Rama Letheby, ing mburi meja, katon minangka [Demure] minangka biarawati.

sentances: We little thought what you were up to, so grave and [Demure] as you both were.
translation: Kita ora mikir apa sing sampeyan lakoni, dadi kuburan lan [Demure] kaya sampeyan.

sentances: For anyone who cared to watch, the event and its [Denouement] provided a graphic demonstration that the Iron Curtain was crumbling.
translation: Kanggo sapa waé sing kepéngin nonton, acara lan [Denouement] nyedhiyakake demonstrasi grafis manawa Tirai Wesi ambruk.

sentances: The bloody [Denouement] his wife had dreaded had come to pass.
translation: Getih [Denouement] bojone sing diwedeni wis kelakon.

sentances: The [Denouement] itself appropriates the theme of the huntsman who spares the child he is obliged to kill.
translation: [Denouement] dhewe cocog karo tema pemburu sing nylametake bocah sing kudu dipateni.

sentances: So says the reawakened Duke Orsino at the [Denouement] of Twelfth Night.
translation: Mangkene pangandikane Adipati Orsino sing wis tangi maneh ing [Denouement] Wengi Rolas.

sentances: It is hardly a shocking [Denouement] to a relationship that seemed doomed virtually from the start.
translation: Iku meh ora ngageti [Denouement] kanggo sesambetan sing ketoke pinasthi sakbenere saka wiwitan.

sentances: The [Denouement] of his history was a tragic one, and had come a few days before the time when our narrative opens.
translation: [Denouement] saka sajarah iku tragis, lan wis teka sawetara dina sadurunge wektu nalika narasi kita mbukak.

sentances: The plot becomes more intense and tragic, as it approaches toward the [Denouement].
translation: Plot dadi luwih kuat lan tragis, amarga nyedhaki [Denouement].

sentances: The hour had now come for the [Denouement] of that home tragedy which was being enacted in the Rue St. Gilles.
translation: Jam saiki wis teka kanggo [Denouement] tragedi omah sing ditindakake ing Rue St. Gilles.

sentances: Our best plan is to remain silent and wait for the [Denouement].
translation: Rencana sing paling apik yaiku meneng lan ngenteni [Denouement].

sentances: Then came the [Denouement]; the marriage arranged for him had been a mockery.
translation: Banjur teka [Denouement]; marriage diatur kanggo wong wis mockery.

sentances: The 28-year-old Sciortino is something of a hipster Jayne Mansfield—busty, unnaturally blonde, and calculatingly [Effervescent].
translation: Sciortino 28 taun iku soko hipster Jayne Mansfield-dadi, unnaturally pirang, lan calculatingly [Effervescent].

sentances: In our interview, Moreno is [Effervescent] and irreverent, with a genuine gift of the gab.
translation: Ing wawancara kita, Moreno [Effervescent] lan ora sopan, kanthi hadiah sing asli saka gab.

sentances: Who was that bubbly, [Effervescent] redhead hosting ‘Chelsea Lately’ on Monday night?
translation: Sapa sing bubbly, [Effervescent] rambut abang hosting 'Chelsea Akhir-akhir iki' ana wengi?

sentances: According to the latest article by Israeli Ambassador Michael Oren, Israeli democracy is “more robust and [Effervescent] than ever.”
translation: Miturut artikel paling anyar dening Duta Besar Israel Michael Oren, demokrasi Israel "luwih kuwat lan [Effervescent] tinimbang sadurunge."

sentances: In contrast to the seriousness and heavy-handedness of late-era Idol, X Factor feels positively [Effervescent].
translation: Beda karo keseriusan lan abot tangan Idol jaman pungkasan, X Factor ngrasa positif [Effervescent].

sentances: Perhaps, as men get older, the [Effervescent] elation of youth leaves them; but they are none the less happy.
translation: Mbok menawa, nalika wong lanang saya tuwa, [Effervescent] elation saka muda ninggalake wong; nanging padha senenge.

sentances: All three were fond of talking, and had many callers who liked to hear the feebly [Effervescent] news of Wellwood.
translation: Katelune padha seneng omong-omongan, lan akeh wong sing nelpon sing seneng ngrungokake kabar Wellwood.

sentances: His style has a certain [Effervescent] quality, but, for all that, the tragic developments of the story are not shirked.
translation: Gayane nduweni kualitas [Effervescent] tartamtu, nanging, kanggo kabeh, perkembangan tragis crita kasebut ora disiram.

sentances: Forbes was in a champagne humor; his soul seemed to be [Effervescent] with little bubbles of joy.
translation: Forbes ana ing banyolan Sampanye; nyawa kang ketoke [Effervescent] karo umpluk sethitik saka bungah.

sentances: His presence acted as a check upon the experimental tendencies of the more [Effervescent] of his subjects.
translation: Ngarsane tumindak minangka mriksa marang kecenderungan eksperimen sing luwih [Effervescent] saka subyek.

sentances: There is something about a firefight at night, something about the mechanical [Elegance] of an M-60 machine gun.
translation: Ana bab firefight ing wayah wengi, soko babagan mechanical [Elegance] saka M-60 machine gun.

sentances: He would have probably done both in much the same way: with [Elegance] and restraint, yet radically.
translation: Dheweke bisa uga nindakake kanthi cara sing padha: kanthi [Elegance] lan ngempet, nanging kanthi radikal.

sentances: This Palmer stands for [Elegance] and sophistication: the embodiment of natural gifts, both athletic and personal.
translation: Palmer iki singkatan saka [Elegance] lan kecanggihan: pawujudan saka peparingé alam, loro atletik lan pribadi.

sentances: Bratis, who trained in Athens, creates pieces of “femininity and pure [Elegance] without artifice.”
translation: Bratis, sing dilatih ing Athena, nggawe potongan "feminitas lan murni [Elegance] tanpa artifice."

sentances: England was almost as good, if mostly in the [Elegance] of their defense.
translation: Inggris meh apik, yen biasane ana ing [Elegance] pertahanane.

sentances: She is always attired in black, and is utterly careless in dress, yet nothing can conceal her innate [Elegance] of figure.
translation: Dheweke tansah nganggo klambi ireng, lan ora sopan nganggo busana, nanging ora ana sing bisa ndhelikake [Elegance] asline.

sentances: After all she, Hilda, possessed some mysterious characteristic more potent than the [Elegance] and the goodness of Janet Orgreave.
translation: Sawise kabeh dheweke, Hilda, duwe sawetara karakteristik misterius sing luwih kuat tinimbang [Elegance] lan kabecikan Janet Orgreave.

sentances: He was distinguished for personal courage, as well as taste for [Elegance] and splendor, whence he was called the munificent.
translation: Dheweke dibedakake amarga keberanian pribadi, uga rasa [Elegance] lan kamulyan, mula dheweke diarani mujijat.

sentances: He wrote verses with [Elegance] in French, Spanish and Italian, and was a polisher of his native language in a barbarous age.
translation: Dheweke nulis syair nganggo [Elegance] ing basa Prancis, Spanyol lan Italia, lan dadi tukang polishing basa ibune ing jaman biadab.

sentances: The [Elegance] of his stature and the pensive melancholy of his classic features invested him with a peculiar power of fascination.
translation: The [Elegance] saka stature lan melankolis pensive saka fitur klasik kang nandur modhal karo daya aneh saka daya tarik.

sentances: Football “is what Plato calls a pharmakon, a poison and an [Elixir],” he writes.
translation: Bal-balan "yaiku sing diarani Plato pharmakon, racun lan [Elixir]," dheweke nulis.

sentances: And the rising star still standing just might be in the best position to offer some [Elixir] to our deeply ailing political system.
translation: Lan lintang sing isih munggah bisa uga ana ing posisi sing paling apik kanggo menehi sawetara [Elixir] menyang sistem politik kita sing lara banget.

sentances: Only she can make hetersoexuality sound like a life-saving [Elixir] that I need to inject directly into my veins.
translation: Mung dheweke bisa nggawe heteroexuality muni kaya nylametake nyawa [Elixir] sing kudu disuntik langsung menyang urat.

sentances: My wife had a very deadly form of cancer, and his story was a powerful [Elixir] that helped us get through it.
translation: Bojoku nandhang penyakit kanker sing mateni, lan critane minangka [Elixir] sing kuat sing mbantu kita ngatasi.

sentances: How a 1,000-year-old fragrant [Elixir] traveled over continents and time to become the signature drink of the Kentucky Derby.
translation: Kepiye wangi [Elixir] umur 1.000 taun ngliwati bawana lan wektu dadi minuman khas Kentucky Derby.

sentances: He is seeking the [Elixir] of long life, for which superior minds have been seeking these two thousand years.
translation: Dheweke nggoleki [Elixir] umur dawa, sing wis digoleki dening pikiran sing unggul rong ewu taun iki.

sentances: Your [Elixir] will not prevent a chimney falling on a man, a bullet going clear through him, or a horse kicking his skull open?
translation: [Elixir] Panjenengan ora bakal nyegah cerobong asep tiba ing wong, peluru arep liwat wong, utawa jaran nendhang tengkorak mbukak?

sentances: I gave him the precious [Elixir] which my mother alone on earth could draw from roots such as no eye of man has ever seen.
translation: Aku menehi dheweke [Elixir] sing larang regane, sing ibuku mung ana ing bumi bisa njupuk saka oyod sing durung tau dideleng dening mripat manungsa.

sentances: Sanatogen, the new [Elixir] of life compounded of casein and glycerophosphates, has been noticed in The Journal from time to time.
translation: Sanatogen, [Elixir] urip anyar sing digabung karo kasein lan gliserofosfat, wis ditemokake ing Jurnal saka wektu kanggo wektu.

sentances: The result was that our friend sent to Kansas for the "[Elixir] of Life."
translation: Asil ana sing kanca kita dikirim kanggo Kansas kanggo "[Elixir] gesang."

sentances: Wall Street Journal: “Begley has a great many strengths—concision, [Eloquence], an eagle eye—and few of the usual shortcomings.”
translation: Wall Street Journal: "Begley duwe akeh kekuwatan - concision, [Eloquence], mripat elang-lan sawetara kekurangan sing biasa."

sentances: And Young, once again with admirable [Eloquence], stands by it.
translation: Lan Young, sepisan maneh karo nggumunake [Eloquence], ngadeg dening iku.

sentances: As sometime Davos attendee Bill Clinton once said, “Explanation is [Eloquence].”
translation: Kaya sing ana ing Davos, Bill Clinton, ujar, "Penjelasan yaiku [Eloquence]."

sentances: He turned his trial into an indictment of apartheid because of his [Eloquence] and passion, but also his training as an advocate.
translation: Dheweke ngowahi pengadilan dadi dakwaan apartheid amarga [Eloquence] lan semangat, nanging uga latihan minangka advokat.

sentances: In his speech, Obama provided some evidence that he plans to lead with action—not merely [Eloquence].
translation: Ing wicarane, Obama nyedhiyakake sawetara bukti yen dheweke arep mimpin kanthi tumindak-ora mung [Eloquence].

sentances: Thomas Cooper, an English prelate, died; highly commended for his great learning and [Eloquence].
translation: Thomas Cooper, prelate Inggris, tilar donya; banget dipuji amarga sinau lan [Eloquence].

sentances: He said no more in words, but his little blue eyes had an [Eloquence] that left nothing to mere speech.
translation: Dheweke ora ngandika maneh ing tembung, nanging mripat biru sethitik duwe [Eloquence] sing ora ninggalake apa-apa kanggo mung wicara.

sentances: He was the friend of Descartes, and a philosopher; distinguished for his [Eloquence] and as an author.
translation: Dheweke kanca Descartes, lan filsuf; dibedakake kanggo [Eloquence] lan minangka penulis.

sentances: He warmly espoused the interests of his country, and many important measures were effected by his [Eloquence].
translation: Dheweke seneng karo kepentingan negarane, lan akeh langkah penting sing ditindakake dening [Eloquence].

sentances: But our [Eloquence] accomplished p. 107little—some small modification regarding mixed trains, and that was all.
translation: Nanging kita [Eloquence] rampung p. 107cilik—sawetara modifikasi cilik babagan sepur campuran, lan mung iku.

sentances: Following an all too predictable cycle of the hyperactive 21st century, focus on the explosion was [Ephemeral].
translation: Sawise siklus sing bisa diprediksi ing abad 21 sing hiperaktif, fokus ing bledosan yaiku [Ephemeral].

sentances: Whatever his approval ratings, the Russian leader knows how [Ephemeral] they can be.
translation: Apa wae peringkat persetujuan, pimpinan Rusia ngerti kepiye [Ephemeral] bisa.

sentances: Most news articles were just as [Ephemeral], but it has become harder to pretend.
translation: Umume artikel warta padha [Ephemeral], nanging dadi luwih angel kanggo pura-pura.

sentances: It may all be [Ephemeral], because most of politics is [Ephemeral], a cynical means to the end of getting elected.
translation: Bisa uga kabeh [Ephemeral], amarga umume politik yaiku [Ephemeral], cara sinis kanggo pungkasane milih.

sentances: But as stimulus goes, the I-stimulus strikes me as a pretty narcissistic and [Ephemeral] one.
translation: Nanging minangka stimulus dadi, I-stimulus nyerang kula minangka cantik narcissistic lan [Ephemeral].

sentances: Do not suppose that I mean to recommend poor music, or feeble, [Ephemeral] compositions.
translation: Aja ngira yen aku arep menehi rekomendasi musik sing ora apik, utawa komposisi [Ephemeral].

sentances: The Widow Lawton ornamented her kitchen floor in a manner as [Ephemeral], though less expensive.
translation: Randha Lawton dekorasi lantai pawon kanthi cara [Ephemeral], sanajan luwih murah.

sentances: Another [Ephemeral] paper, L'Italia del Popolo, was launched on its short career.
translation: Makalah [Ephemeral] liyane, L'Italia del Popolo, diluncurake ing karir sing cendhak.

sentances: They were, no doubt, chiefly of a pantomimic and [Ephemeral] kind.
translation: Dheweke, mesthi, utamane saka jinis pantomimik lan [Ephemeral].

sentances: But like all dunghill products, the life of these was [Ephemeral].
translation: Nanging kaya kabeh produk dunghill, urip iki [Ephemeral].

sentances: Richard Kurin was a 19-year-old anthropology student in India when he experienced his material culture [Epiphany].
translation: Richard Kurin minangka mahasiswa antropologi 19 taun ing India nalika ngalami budaya material [Epiphany].

sentances: Zaks experienced an [Epiphany] of sorts a couple years ago, when he was looking through a book of Tony Walton illustrations.
translation: Zaks ngalami [Epiphany] sawetara taun kepungkur, nalika dheweke nggoleki buku ilustrasi Tony Walton.

sentances: While watching The Ten Commandments on TV with their children for the umpteenth time, Burnett and Downey had an [Epiphany].
translation: Nalika nonton The Ten Commandments ing TV karo anak-anake kanggo kaping sepuluh, Burnett lan Downey duwe [Epiphany].

sentances: This was an [Epiphany], this was imprinted on you, you could do anything now.
translation: Iki minangka [Epiphany], iki dicithak ing sampeyan, sampeyan bisa nindakake apa wae saiki.

sentances: The teenager went to rehab, and then went right back to using—until he had an [Epiphany].
translation: Remaja kasebut pindhah menyang rehab, lan banjur bali menyang nggunakake-nganti dheweke duwe [Epiphany].

sentances: Their escape was made at midnight on the eve of [Epiphany], 1649, all the court following in great disorder.
translation: Uwal kasebut ditindakake ing tengah wengi ing wayah wengi [Epiphany], 1649, kabeh pengadilan ngetutake gangguan gedhe.

sentances: Neophytes should therefore be baptized at Easter and Pentecost alone, never at [Epiphany].
translation: Mulane Neophytes kudu dibaptis ing Paskah lan Pentakosta piyambak, ora tau ing [Epiphany].

sentances: So careful is the poet to prepare both sides—the divine [Epiphany], and the mortal who is to behold it.
translation: Dadi ati-ati pujangga kanggo nyiapake loro-lorone - gaib [Epiphany], lan fana sing bakal weruh.

sentances: He thought the lessons of the Nativity and [Epiphany] came as a very wholesome corrective to these tendencies.
translation: Dheweke ngira piwulang babagan Nativity lan [Epiphany] minangka koreksi sing apik banget kanggo kecenderungan kasebut.

sentances: There is nothing of him now in Florence, save a few drawings in the Uffizi and an unfinished picture of the [Epiphany].
translation: Ora ana apa-apa saka dheweke saiki ing Florence, nyimpen sawetara gambar ing Uffizi lan gambar sing durung rampung saka [Epiphany].

sentances: After what seemed a desperate [Eternity], a doctor shook his head.
translation: Sawise apa sing katon nekat [Eternity], dhokter geleng-geleng kepala.

sentances: The Newsroom aired its final episode on Sunday, already an [Eternity] ago in news-cycle terms.
translation: The Newsroom ditayangke episode pungkasan ing dina Minggu, wis [Eternity] kepungkur ing istilah siklus warta.

sentances: He rests lavishly, depicted in a marble sarcophagus that stares up for [Eternity] at the carved depictions of his life story.
translation: Dheweke santai banget, digambarake ing sarcophagus marmer sing mentheleng [Eternity] ing gambaran sing diukir saka crita uripe.

sentances: But this is also a parody of narcissism, just a little detour to [Eternity].
translation: Nanging iki uga parodi saka narcissism, mung detour sethitik kanggo [Eternity].

sentances: Finally, after an [Eternity]—lasting maybe two seconds—I did what I usually do when faced with fear squatting in my stomach.
translation: Pungkasan, sawise [Kelanggengan] - bisa uga rong detik - aku nindakake apa sing biasane daklakoni nalika ngadhepi rasa wedi squatting ing weteng.

sentances: The blessings of time and [Eternity] constitute the part of the promise offered to believers, through Christ.
translation: Berkah wektu lan [Langgeng] minangka bagean saka janji sing ditawakake kanggo wong-wong sing percaya, liwat Kristus.

sentances: One instant in all [Eternity] would have made just the difference between life and death to you.
translation: Siji instan ing kabeh [Kalanggengan] bakal nggawe prabédan antarane urip lan pati kanggo sampeyan.

sentances: He who wrongs a fellow-creature wrongs himself as well, and wrongs both for all [Eternity].
translation: Sapa sing nganiaya marang sesama makhluk, dheweke uga nganiaya awake dhewe, lan nglanggar loro-lorone kanggo kabeh [Kalanggengan].

sentances: At the close of the supper he filled his glass, and rising, proposed to drink to the [Eternity] of the Republic.
translation: Ing pungkasan nedha bengi dheweke ngisi gelas, lan munggah, ngusulake ngombe menyang [Kalanggengan] Republik.

sentances: An [Eternity] did it seem before those men returned and marched once more over his head.
translation: [Kelanggengan] katon sadurunge wong-wong mau bali lan mlaku maneh ing sirahe.

sentances: Bitcoin began 2013 with a roaring price of $770 per unit, and businesses right and left were converting to the [Ethereal] product.
translation: Bitcoin wiwit 2013 kanthi rega $ 770 saben unit, lan bisnis tengen lan kiwa padha ngowahi menyang produk [Ethereal].

sentances: But when modern-day conservationists surveyed the offshore rocks they discovered something even more [Ethereal] lurking within.
translation: Nanging nalika konservasionis modern nliti watu lepas pantai, dheweke nemokake sing luwih [Ethereal] sing ana ing njero.

sentances: One skeleton in particular has become famous for the brutal way she died and the [Ethereal] way her body was preserved.
translation: Salah sawijining balung utamane wis misuwur amarga cara brutal dheweke seda lan cara [Ethereal] awak dilestarekake.

sentances: C, lastly, I just think [Perritaz] has a natural taste for purity, delicacy, and [Ethereal] balance.
translation: C, pamungkas, aku mung mikir [Perritaz] nduweni rasa alami kanggo kemurnian, kelezatan, lan keseimbangan [Ethereal].

sentances: I remember telling people at the time, ‘This kid is so [Ethereal] and interesting.’
translation: Aku elinga ngandhani wong-wong ing wektu iku, 'Bocah iki pancen [Ethereal] lan menarik.'

sentances: Her white face looked [Ethereal] in the moonlight, and her bloodless lips were quivering with returning life.
translation: Pasuryane putih katon [Ethereal] ing cahya rembulan, lan lambene sing ora ana getihe quivering karo urip bali.

sentances: It may be applied directly to a suspected fluid, or, better, to the [Ethereal] extract.
translation: Bisa ditrapake langsung menyang cairan sing dicurigai, utawa, luwih apik, menyang ekstrak [Ethereal].

sentances: And as she hesitated between obedience to one and duty toward the other, her life, her [Love] and future was in the balance.
translation: Lan nalika dheweke ragu-ragu antarane manut siji lan tugas marang liyane, uripe, dheweke [Tresna] lan masa depan ana ing imbangan.

sentances: Nothing but an extreme [Love] of truth could have hindered me from concealing this part of my story.
translation: Ora ana apa-apa kajaba [Cinta] bebener sing bisa ngalangi aku ora ndhelikake bagean critaku iki.

sentances: But then that night, Dad played it back to me in bed, like a [Lullaby], my own recorded voice singing myself to sleep.
translation: Nanging ing wayah wengi, Bapak muter maneh ing amben, kaya [Lullaby], swaraku sing direkam nyanyi dhewe nganti turu.

sentances: Washington loves a [Lullaby]—like the one about both sides deserving blame for the decline in bipartisanship.
translation: Washington seneng [Lullaby] - kaya sing ana ing sisih loro sing kudu disalahake amarga nyuda bipartisan.

sentances: Gervais sings Elmo a “celebrity [Lullaby]” and even offers him a “celebrity cup of milk.”
translation: Gervais nembangake Elmo minangka "selebriti [Lullaby]" lan malah menehi dheweke "cangkir susu selebriti."

sentances: It was depressing to think of going to bed in such circumstances with the yelling of an Arctic storm for a [Lullaby].
translation: Iku depressing kanggo mikir arep turu ing kahanan kuwi karo bengok-bengok saka badai Arktik kanggo [Lullaby].

sentances: A child's preference for the mother's singing is, perhaps, a half reminiscence of the soft-low tones of the [Lullaby].
translation: Preferensi bocah kanggo nembang ibune, bisa uga, setengah ngeling-eling nada sing lembut saka [Lullaby].

sentances: Twas a quiet sea, breaking, in crooning [Lullaby], upon the rocks below my bedroom window.
translation: Twas segara sepi, bejat, ing crooning [Lullaby], ing rocks ngisor jendela kamarku.

sentances: The night winds sing her [Lullaby], and little children hear the music of her voice and look into her answering eyes.
translation: Angin wengi nyanyi dheweke [Lullaby], lan bocah-bocah cilik krungu musik swarane lan ndeleng mripate sing mangsuli.

sentances: She gave the gun to Polly, and told her to walk up and down the porch with it and sing a [Lullaby].
translation: Dheweke menehi bedhil kanggo Polly, lan marang dheweke kanggo lumaku munggah lan mudhun emper karo lan sing a [Lullaby].

sentances: Tim said to me, “What if someone took a picture on their iPad and then used this method to turn iPad [Luminescence] into oil paint?”
translation: Tim kandha marang aku, "Apa yen ana wong sing njupuk gambar ing iPad banjur nggunakake cara iki kanggo ngowahi iPad [Luminescence] dadi cat minyak?"

sentances: And, ironically, in the darkness, he sees the [Luminescence] of the jungle around him.
translation: Lan, ironis, ing pepeteng, dheweke ndeleng [Luminescence] alas ing saubengé.

sentances: It glowed in the room with a pearly [Luminescence], and she saw the man's eyes turning to it, drawn as if by magic.
translation: Iku cemlorot ing kamar karo mutiara [Luminescence], lan dheweke weruh mripate wong kang nguripake kanggo iku, digambar kaya sihir.

sentances: The [Luminescence] died; there was no longer light enough to penetrate to his helmet's darkened goggles.
translation: [Luminescence] seda; ora ana cahya maneh sing bisa nembus kaca tingal helm sing peteng.

sentances: His left hand fell upon Assha's shoulder, turning the man half around as Ross, too, stepped upon the patch of [Luminescence].
translation: Tangane kiwa tiba ing pundhake Assha, ngowahi wong kasebut setengah nalika Ross, uga, mlaku ing tembelan [Luminescence].

sentances: Then, swiftly as it had come, it was gone, and only a small globe of white [Luminescence] floated above the great hulking machine.
translation: Banjur, kanthi cepet kaya wis teka, iku ilang, lan mung globe cilik putih [Luminescence] ngambang ing ndhuwur mesin hulking gedhe.

sentances: Hungrily the Earth man stared at his distant flash pistols, plainly visible in the [Luminescence] of their fungus bedding.
translation: Wong Bumi kanthi luwe ndeleng pistol kilat sing adoh, katon jelas ing [Luminescence] sprei jamur.

sentances: From a [Lyrical] standpoint, there are precious few that can catch Kendrick.
translation: Saka sudut [Lyrical], ana sawetara larang regane sing bisa nyekel Kendrick.

sentances: I promised never again to wax [Lyrical] about the fries in gravy.
translation: Aku janji ora bakal maneh lilin [Lirik] babagan goreng ing saus.

sentances: He loved simplicity in his musical arrangements, which allowed his [Lyrical] message and melodies to shine through.
translation: Panjenenganipun tresna gamblang ing aransemen musik, kang ngidini [Lyrical] pesen lan melodi kanggo kawentar liwat.

sentances: The [Lyrical] declamation has inspired luminaries ranging from Kurt Vonnegut to Robert Frost.
translation: Deklamasi [Lyrical] wis inspirasi luminaries wiwit saka Kurt Vonnegut kanggo Robert Frost.

sentances: This dad read it as the latter and wrote his own [Lyrical] rebuttal to the tune.
translation: Bapak iki maca minangka sing terakhir lan nulis dhewe [Lyrical] rebuttal kanggo tune.

sentances: True hymns are sacred lyrics, and a lyric to be [Lyrical] and heart appealing, must be inevitable.
translation: Hymns sejati iku lirik suci, lan lirik sing dadi [Lirik] lan narik ati, mesthine ora bisa dihindari.

sentances: But what of the love, however expressed, in the [Lyrical] invocation to the brown liqueur?
translation: Nanging apa katresnan, nanging ditulis, ing [Lyrical] invocation kanggo liqueur coklat?

sentances: Who shall sing in [Lyrical] language the exhilaration of such splendid men's work?
translation: Sapa sing bakal nyanyi nganggo basa [lirik] kesenengan karya wong sing apik banget?

sentances: Still, Andronicus was the first to substitute the Greek drama for the old [Lyrical] stage poetry.
translation: Nanging, Andronicus minangka sing pisanan ngganti drama Yunani kanggo puisi panggung [Lirik] lawas.

sentances: In [Lyrical] poetry, the Romans can boast of one of the greatest masters of any age or nation.
translation: Ing puisi [Lyrical], wong Romawi bisa gumunggung salah sawijining master paling gedhe ing umur utawa bangsa.

sentances: I found their [Melancholy] inviting and I appreciated their contemplative, lonely world.
translation: Aku nemokake dheweke [Melancholy] ngundang lan aku ngormati jagad sing kontemplatif lan sepi.

sentances: In the first chapter, rebellious Holly Sykes runs away from home and headlong into the [Melancholy] perils of first love.
translation: Ing bab pisanan, mbrontak Holly Sykes mlayu saka ngarep lan headlong menyang [Melancholy] perils saka katresnan pisanan.

sentances: "Ah, that trip with Lance," he said, then glanced down, with those [Melancholy] eyes.
translation: "Ah, lelungan karo Lance," ujare, banjur nglirik, kanthi mripat [Melankolis].

sentances: The slurring of relationships and transactions has effects ranging from the gruesome to the [Melancholy].
translation: Ing slurring sesambetan lan transaksi wis efek kiro-kiro saka gruesome kanggo [Melancholy].

sentances: Young and gracious faces, somewhat remote and proud, but with a [Melancholy] and sweet kindness.
translation: Pasuryan enom lan grapyak, rada adoh lan bangga, nanging kanthi kebecikan [Melankolis] lan manis.

sentances: But, when the car came thundering down, it was crammed to the step; with a [Melancholy] gesture, the driver declined her signal.
translation: Nanging, nalika mobil teka thundered mudhun, iku crammed kanggo langkah; karo patrap [Melankolis], sopir nolak sinyal dheweke.

sentances: At the same time he is appreciative and very amusing, and one has no chance to indulge in [Melancholy] with him.
translation: Ing wektu sing padha, dheweke ngapresiasi lan nyenengake banget, lan ora ana kesempatan kanggo nyenengi [Melancholy] karo dheweke.

sentances: Quaint old Burton in his "Anatomy of [Melancholy]," recognizes the virtues of the plant while he anathematizes its abuse.
translation: Burton lawas sing aneh ing "Anatomi [Melankolis]," ngakoni kabecikan tanduran kasebut nalika dheweke anathematizes penyalahgunaan.

sentances: There is among women always a [Melancholy] satisfaction in seeing the very last of the beloved object.
translation: Ana ing antarane wanita tansah kepuasan [Melancholy] ing ndeleng pungkasan banget saka obyek kinasih.

sentances: There is nothing like it among us at the present day except within the [Melancholy] precincts of the penitentiary.
translation: Ora ana sing kaya ngono ing antarane kita ing jaman saiki, kajaba ing wilayah [Melankolis] penjara.

sentances: In or out of uniform his motion is languid, his voice relaxed and [Mellifluous], his movements deliberate, confident.
translation: Ing utawa metu saka seragam gerakane languid, swarane santai lan [Mellifluous], gerakane disengaja, yakin.

sentances: And Costas is, after all, a guy who is famous for his [Mellifluous] commentary on balls and strikes, touchdowns and field goals.
translation: Lan Costas, sawise kabeh, wong sing misuwur kanthi komentar [Mellifluous] babagan bal lan serangan, touchdown lan gol lapangan.

sentances: By the time she had taken in so much as this the [Mellifluous] young man had perceived and addressed himself to her brother.
translation: Ing wektu dheweke wis njupuk ing dadi luwih kaya iki [Mellifluous] wong enom wis perceived lan ono piyambak kanggo adhine.

sentances: And the banks of those rivers resounded with the [Mellifluous] strains of the male Kokilas and the notes of peacocks and cranes.
translation: Lan pinggir-pinggir kali iku gumuruh karo [Mellifluous] galur Kokilas lanang lan cathetan saka manuk merak lan crane.

sentances: One is not surprised at their being addressed by such [Mellifluous] epithets as Cushla machree, asthore, mavourneen!
translation: Siji ora kaget nalika ditangani dening epithets [Mellifluous] kayata Cushla machree, asthore, mavourneen!

sentances: No, no; change churlish dreams and braving trumpets to [Mellifluous] flutes.
translation: Ora, ora; ngganti impen churlish lan slompret braving kanggo [Mellifluous] suling.

sentances: Though she had spoken quite sharply at the telephone, her voice was [Mellifluous] when she attuned it to Gabriella.
translation: Sanadyan dheweke wis ngandika cukup cetha ing telpon, dheweke swara [Mellifluous] nalika dheweke attuned kanggo Gabriella.

sentances: But a funny thing happened on the way to the funeral: a [Miraculous] resurrection!
translation: Nanging ana kedadeyan sing lucu ing dalan menyang panguburan: kebangkitan [Ajaib]!

sentances: A volunteer I spoke to at length, Julia Cohen, explained to me that the [Miraculous] power of Amma is her intuitiveness.
translation: Relawan sing dakkandhakake kanthi dawa, Julia Cohen, nerangake manawa kekuwatan [Ajaib] Amma minangka intuisi dheweke.

sentances: The [Miraculous] brand of Billy-the-Fish football is almost over and the butch giants are back.
translation: Merek [Ajaib] bal-balan Billy-the-Fish meh rampung lan raksasa butch bali.

sentances: While no one doubts that Diaz is healed, surviving brain aneurysms is not exactly [Miraculous].
translation: Nalika ora ana sing mangu-mangu yen Diaz wis waras, aneurisma otak sing isih urip ora persis [Ajaib].

sentances: Inside her [Miraculous] recovery and her fight against returning to Afghanistan.
translation: Ing njero dheweke [Miraculous] pulih lan dheweke perang nglawan bali menyang Afghanistan.

sentances: To Indians that appears a [Miraculous] thing, beyond what is either acquired or natural.
translation: Kanggo wong India sing katon minangka [Ajaib], ngluwihi apa sing dipikolehi utawa alami.

sentances: Hilda, once more and in a higher degree, realized the [Miraculous] human power to make experience out of nothing.
translation: Hilda, sepisan maneh lan ing tingkat sing luwih dhuwur, nyadari kekuwatan manungsa [Ajaib] kanggo nggawe pengalaman saka apa-apa.

sentances: The fact alleged, then, is [Miraculous] and important, and the evidence in proof of such a fact should be overwhelmingly strong.
translation: Kasunyatan sing miturut omongane uwong iku [Ajaib] lan penting, lan bukti bukti kasunyatan kasebut kudu kuwat banget.

sentances: Joan was calmer now, and her mother had put on some warmer, and less [Miraculous], garments.
translation: Joan saiki luwih tenang, lan ibune wis nganggo sandhangan sing luwih anget, lan kurang [Ajaib].

sentances: Miss Anne went on to talk of Jean, a [Miraculous] infant of infinite graces and accomplishments.
translation: Miss Anne banjur ngomong babagan Jean, bayi [Ajaib] sing tanpa wates lan prestasi.

sentances: Sometimes politicians oppose reform for [Nefarious] reasons—to protect a special interest or a major donor, for example.
translation: Kadhangkala politisi nentang reformasi amarga alasan [Nefarious]—kanggo nglindhungi kapentingan khusus utawa donor utama, contone.

sentances: The Arabs offered the Nazis a haven, as well as a market for all their [Nefarious] dealings in arms and black market currency.
translation: Wong Arab nawani Nazi minangka papan perlindungan, uga minangka pasar kanggo kabeh transaksi [Nefarious] ing senjata lan mata uang pasar gelap.

sentances: Rumors swirled that the McStays had gone into Mexico and were involved in [Nefarious] dealings with drug cartels.
translation: Gosip swirled sing McStays wis musna menyang Meksiko lan padha melu [Nefarious] urusan karo cartels tamba.

sentances: But Green-Wood is more famous for its [Nefarious] residents, those of the drug-peddling, political-swindling, hit-men variety.
translation: Nanging Green-Wood luwih misuwur kanggo warga [Nefarious] sawijining, sing saka tamba-peddling, politik-swindling, macem-macem hit-man.

sentances: Greece claims they were looted from the Parthenon by a [Nefarious] British Indiana Jones character in the early 1800s.
translation: Yunani ngaku padha dijarah saka Parthenon dening [Nefarious] karakter Indiana Jones Inggris ing awal 1800s.

sentances: Some were even re-arrested for the same [Nefarious] purpose, and the daily papers published their names on each occasion.
translation: Sawetara malah dicekel maneh kanggo tujuan [Nefarious] sing padha, lan koran saben dina nerbitake jenenge ing saben kesempatan.

sentances: There, if his eyes did not deceive him, were evidences of mortar dislodged by [Nefarious] toes.
translation: Ing kono, yen mripate ora ngapusi dheweke, ana bukti mortir sing dicopot dening driji sikil [Nefarious].

sentances: She was to join him a week later, after he had had time to spy out the land and make his [Nefarious] schemes for a mock marriage.
translation: Dheweke bakal gabung karo dheweke seminggu sabanjure, sawise dheweke duwe wektu kanggo Spy tanah lan nggawe rencana [Nefarious] kanggo nikah mock.

sentances: It wasn't built by Green, but by a former owner of the farm, who was in the same [Nefarious] business.
translation: Iku ora dibangun dening Green, nanging dening mantan pemilik saka farm, sing ing padha [Nefarious] bisnis.

sentances: This is, then, what Bond artifice effected in the absence of actual cause and in order to dissimulate its own [Nefarious] objects.
translation: Iki, banjur, apa Bond artifice effected ing anané sabab nyata lan supaya dissimulate dhewe [Nefarious] obyek.

sentances: He finally died in a drawn-out battle with his Irish mobster [Nemesis], John Morrissey.
translation: Dheweke pungkasane tiwas ing perang sing ditarik karo mobster Irlandia [Nemesis], John Morrissey.

sentances: The Third Reich met its [Nemesis] as much here as it had—albeit in far greater numbers—at Stalingrad.
translation: Reich Katelu nemoni [Nemesis] ing kene - sanajan luwih akeh - ing Stalingrad.

sentances: Neither her name nor her [Nemesis] are among the slurred words I can make out.
translation: Sanadyan jeneng dheweke utawa dheweke [Nemesis] kalebu tembung-tembung sing ora bisa dingerteni.

sentances: The [Nemesis] that emerges most potently is that of reality TV.
translation: [Nemesis] sing muncul paling kuat yaiku realita TV.

sentances: The site is provocative enough in the vegan world to earn its own digital arch-[Nemesis] “30 Bananas A Day…Sucks!”
translation: Situs kasebut cukup provokatif ing jagad vegan kanggo entuk arch digital dhewe-[Nemesis] "30 Bananas A Day… Nyedhot!"

sentances: We have swift reward and punishment—no hateful things called [Nemesis].
translation: Kita duwe ganjaran lan paukuman sing cepet - ora ana barang sing disengiti sing diarani [Nemesis].

sentances: Then, as though grown weary of the idyllic romance she was composing, Fortune donned the tragic robes of [Nemesis].
translation: Banjur, kaya bosen karo romansa idyllic sing dikarang, Fortune nganggo jubah tragis [Nemesis].

sentances: What was the tragic destiny that hung over them—the [Nemesis] that gripped them, and forced them to take such a chance?
translation: Apa nasib tragis sing ana ing dheweke - [Nemesis] sing nyekel dheweke, lan meksa dheweke njupuk kesempatan kasebut?

sentances: When off the island of Moora the [Nemesis] came suddenly upon a fleet of eleven pirate boats, pursuing a trading prahu.
translation: Nalika metu saka pulo Moora, [Nemesis] dumadakan teka ing armada bajak laut sawelas, nguber prahu dagang.

sentances: The [Nemesis] chased the pirates to the shore, who drew up in line along the beach.
translation: [Nemesis] ngoyak para bajak laut menyang pinggir pantai, sing nggawe garis ing pinggir pantai.

sentances: If opponents of gay rights are supposed to be retreating into [Oblivion], they missed the memo.
translation: Yen mungsuh hak gay mesthine bakal mundur menyang [Oblivion], dheweke ora kejawab memo kasebut.

sentances: The team could sink into [Oblivion]—or be bought by a beloved figure who could transform it.
translation: Tim kasebut bisa tenggelam ing [Oblivion] - utawa dituku dening tokoh sing ditresnani sing bisa ngowahi.

sentances: That which gave him the power over me came back out of [Oblivion], where I had hoped to keep it.
translation: Kang paring panguwasa marang aku iku bali saka [Oblivion], ing ngendi aku ngarep-arep kanggo nyimpen.

sentances: Instead, one is headed to political [Oblivion], and the other is staring it in its face.
translation: Nanging, sing siji tumuju menyang [Oblivion] politik, lan sing liyane lagi mandeng.

sentances: Not even a plan: just a wild lashing out, really, against [Oblivion].
translation: Ora malah rencana: mung lashing alam bébas metu, tenan, marang [Oblivion].

sentances: He was contemporary with Milton, and preferred before him by critics of the day, but has now sunk into [Oblivion].
translation: Dheweke kontemporer karo Milton, lan luwih disenengi dening para kritikus jaman saiki, nanging saiki wis tenggelam ing [Oblivion].

sentances: Could you have let them alone, by this time, poor Souls, they had been all peaceably buried in [Oblivion]!
translation: Apa sampeyan bisa nglilani wong-wong mau, ing wektu iki, Jiwa-jiwa miskin, kabeh wis dikubur kanthi tentrem ing [Oblivion]!

sentances: After the total [Oblivion] of the matter in his waking moments, he will sometimes recall all the details of the affair in a dream.
translation: Sawise total [Oblivion] saka prakara ing wayahe tangi, kang kadhangkala bakal kelingan kabeh rincian urusan ing ngimpi.

sentances: Sleep kindly came to some, and lulled their spirits into momentary [Oblivion].
translation: Turu kanthi nyenengake sawetara wong, lan nggumunake semangate nganti sedhela [Oblivion].

sentances: Holding the violin aloft, he cried exultingly: Henceforth thou art mine, though death and [Oblivion] lurk ever near thee!
translation: Sambil nyepeng biola ing dhuwur, dheweke nguwuh kanthi bungah: Wiwit saiki kowe dadi duwekku, sanajan pati lan [Lali] tansah cedhak karo kowe!

sentances: He seemed as much taken aback as if he had found a tribe of Cherokees studying [Onomatopoeia] in English verse.
translation: Dheweke katon kaget kaya dheweke nemokake suku Cherokees sing sinau [Onomatopoeia] ing ayat Inggris.

sentances: All words which were spontaneously acquired seemed to be instances of [Onomatopoeia].
translation: Kabeh tembung sing dipikolehi kanthi spontan katon minangka conto saka [Onomatopoeia].

sentances: [Onomatopoeia], formations of words resembling in sound that of the things denoted by them.
translation: [Onomatopoeia], tatanan tembung sing meh padha karo swara saka barang-barang kasebut.

sentances: Mao, the term for a "cat," is obviously an example of [Onomatopoeia].
translation: Mao, istilah kanggo "kucing," jelas minangka conto saka [Onomatopoeia].

sentances: This correspondence of sound and sense is called [Onomatopoeia].
translation: Korespondensi swara lan rasa iki diarani [Onomatopoeia].

sentances: We see it at several different periods, from the height of its [Opulence] in the 1930s to the shabby Communist look of the 1960s.
translation: Kita ndeleng ing sawetara wektu sing beda-beda, saka dhuwur [Opulence] ing taun 1930-an nganti tampilan Komunis sing kumuh ing taun 1960-an.

sentances: The scale, [Opulence] and fantasy so prevalent a few miles away on the Strip is nowhere to be found.
translation: Skala, [Opulence] lan Fantasi dadi lazim sawetara mil adoh ing Strip ora ono.

sentances: Many say that The Great Beauty is the new Fellini, with its handsome surrealism, baroque expressions, and casual [Opulence].
translation: Akeh sing ngomong yen The Great Beauty minangka Fellini anyar, kanthi surrealisme sing nggantheng, ekspresi barok, lan santai [Opulence].

sentances: The Daily Pic: The Met's Cloisters branch turns 75, and shows off knightly [Opulence].
translation: The Daily Pic: The Met's Cloisters cabang dadi 75, lan nuduhake ksatria [Opulence].

sentances: The [Opulence] of the gifts is legendary, and it used to be that the presenters and performers at the ceremony also received them.
translation: The [Opulence] peparingé iku legendaris, lan biyen sing presenter lan pemain ing upacara uga nampa iku.

sentances: There were hundreds of thousands in France, the most illustrious in rank and [Opulence], who would join such an army.
translation: Ana atusan ewu ing Prancis, sing paling misuwur ing pangkat lan [Opulence], sing bakal gabung karo tentara kasebut.

sentances: [Opulence] introduced the cultivation of the fine arts, with a taste for literature, and consequently for disputation.
translation: [Opulence] ngenalake budidaya seni rupa, kanthi rasa sastra, lan mulane kanggo regejegan.

sentances: There are beings so dejected—so penurious—that this swearing constitutes their whole store of worldly [Opulence].
translation: Ana makhluk sing sedhih banget - banget kesel - nganti sumpah iki dadi kabeh nyimpen kadonyan [Opulence].

sentances: The emigrant from the sandbanks of Cape Cod revels in the profusion of the [Opulence] of Ohio.
translation: Emigrants saka sandbanks Cape Cod revels ing profusion saka [Opulence] Ohio.

sentances: Hundreds of families were burned out, and reduced from [Opulence], or at least competency, to penury.
translation: Atusan kulawarga diobong, lan dikurangi saka [Opulence], utawa paling ora kompetensi, dadi kemiskinan.

sentances: But I feel like films are uniquely suited towards addressing [Paradox], recursiveness, and worlds-within-worlds.
translation: Nanging aku rumangsa kaya film sing cocog karo [Paradox], rekursif, lan jagad-ing-donya.

sentances: To appreciate the Palmer [Paradox], it's important to understand that Palmer's childhood and young adulthood were dichotomous.
translation: Kanggo ngurmati Palmer [Paradox], penting kanggo ngerti yen bocah cilik lan diwasa Palmer dikotomi.

sentances: “Maybe we need a new category other than theism, atheism or agnosticism that takes [Paradox] and unknowing into account,” he writes.
translation: "Mungkin kita butuh kategori anyar liyane saka teisme, ateisme utawa agnostisisme sing njupuk [Paradox] lan ora ngerti," tulise.

sentances: But Washington was a prisoner to its [Paradox] of an Iraq policy.
translation: Nanging Washington dadi tawanan kanggo [Paradox] kabijakan Irak.

sentances: As a result of this [Paradox], the Iraq policy process ground to a halt at the very moment that ISIS was on the rise.
translation: Minangka asil [Paradox] iki, proses kabijakan Irak mandheg nalika ISIS saya mundhak.

sentances: It offers, to those who see it aright, the most perplexing industrial [Paradox] ever presented in the history of mankind.
translation: Nawakake, kanggo sing ndeleng kanthi bener, industri [Paradox] sing paling mbingungake sing nate ditampilake ing sejarah manungsa.

sentances: But in reality this [Paradox] of value is the most fundamental proposition in economic science.
translation: Nanging ing kasunyatan iki [Paradoks] nilai minangka proposisi paling dhasar ing ilmu ekonomi.

sentances: It was the spiritual way, whose method and secret lie in that subtle [Paradox]: Yield to conquer.
translation: Iku cara spiritual, kang cara lan rahasia dumunung ing subtle [Paradox]: Ngasilake kanggo nelukake.

sentances: But it was a strange [Paradox], that precisely the depth of his love for her made him willing to think of losing her.
translation: Nanging iku aneh [Paradox], sing sabenere ambane katresnan kanggo dheweke nggawe dheweke gelem mikir kelangan dheweke.

sentances: But this very [Paradox] leads to the real principle of generalization concerning the properties of numbers.
translation: Nanging iki banget [Paradox] ndadékaké kanggo prinsip nyata generalisasi bab sifat nomer.

sentances: Domestically, the prime minister maintains the dubious line that he is the only man who can keep the still-fragile [Peace].

translation: Nada kasebut pisanan dhuwur, banjur kurang, ora tau guttural, lan nduweni kualitas [Sibilant] tartamtu.

sentances: The coat, with fitted bodice, nipped-in waist, and full skirt, created a familiar [Silhouette] for Kate.
translation: Jas kasebut, kanthi bodice sing dipasang, pinggul sing dicepit, lan rok lengkap, nggawe [Siluet] sing akrab kanggo Kate.

sentances: I would have added “no photographs of meditative politicians walking on the shore” with a slash though a [Silhouette] of JFK.
translation: Aku bakal nambah "ora ana foto politisi meditative mlaku-mlaku ing pantai" kanthi garis miring sanajan ana [Siluet] JFK.

sentances: As you walk in front of the first screen, your [Silhouette] appears and birds swoop down toward you.
translation: Nalika sampeyan lumaku ing ngarepe layar pisanan, [Siluet] sampeyan katon lan manuk-manuk mlayu marani sampeyan.

sentances: And I sat there as he shot the [Silhouette], but he had to stop because I started frantically crying.
translation: Lan aku lungguh ing kono nalika dheweke nembak [Siluet], nanging dheweke kudu mandheg amarga aku wiwit nangis.

sentances: She picks out Diane von Furstenberg dresses and starts really enjoying this new [Silhouette], this new freedom.
translation: Dheweke milih gaun Diane von Furstenberg lan wiwit seneng banget [Siluet] anyar iki, kebebasan anyar iki.

sentances: In the dimly-lighted doorway of a corner house the figure of a Chinaman showed as a motionless [Silhouette].
translation: Ing lawang omah pojok sing surem cahya katon sosok wong China minangka [Siluet] sing ora obah.

sentances: It was then easy enough to obtain a fairly accurate [Silhouette], by either outlining the profile or cutting it out from the screen.
translation: Iku banjur cukup gampang kanggo njupuk cukup akurat [Siluet], dening salah siji outlining profil utawa Cut metu saka layar.

sentances: He existed, moreover, only in contour; he never rose above harmoniously outlined [Silhouette].
translation: Dheweke ana, malih, mung ing kontur; dheweke ora tau munggah ing ndhuwur kanthi harmonis [Siluet].

sentances: Pete produced the [Silhouette] of a young lady, and handed it round.
translation: Pete ngasilake [Siluet] saka wanita enom, lan nyerahke bunder.

sentances: Looking in the same direction I saw, through the haze, the sharp outlines of a city in gray [Silhouette].
translation: Nggoleki ing arah sing padha aku weruh, liwat kabut, garis cetha saka kutha ing werna abu-abu [Siluet].

sentances: Perhaps some of that [Solitude] and bitterness found its way into Alec Leamas.
translation: Mbok menawa sawetara saka [Solitude] lan pait nemu dalan menyang Alec Leamas.

sentances: The Dude is at his happiest when he has a few minutes of [Solitude] and rest to get high and listen to whale sounds.
translation: Wong lanang iku paling seneng nalika dheweke duwe sawetara menit [Solitude] lan ngaso kanggo dhuwur lan ngrungokake swara paus.

sentances: [Solitude] activates the imagination, and invites introspection.
translation: [Solitude] ngaktifake imajinasi, lan ngajak introspeksi.

sentances: Adam (Tom Hiddleston), the vampire composer, seeks [Solitude] and people willing to trade him his blood fix.
translation: Adam (Tom Hiddleston), komposer vampir, ngupaya [Solitude] lan wong-wong sing gelem perdagangan dheweke ndandani getih.

sentances: If you thought qualifications for being a hermit were a tendency toward [Solitude] and dislike of civilization, think again.
translation: Yen sampeyan ngira kualifikasi dadi pertapa minangka kecenderungan kanggo [Solitude] lan ora seneng karo peradaban, pikirake maneh.

sentances: Was he really condemned to an eternal [Solitude] because of the girl who had died so many years ago?
translation: Apa dheweke pancen dikutuk dadi [Solitude] sing langgeng amarga bocah wadon sing wis mati pirang-pirang taun kepungkur?

sentances: Prud'hon, in humiliation and despair, lived in a [Solitude] almost complete.
translation: Prud'hon, ing asor lan putus asa, urip ing [Solitude] meh rampung.

sentances: He walked on, and thought of the rapt liberty of the soul in the sweet serenities of beautiful [Solitude].
translation: Dheweke mlaku terus, lan mikirake kamardikan rapt saka nyawa ing serenities manis ayu [Solitude].

sentances: No, poor thing, I fear she has anxieties of her own just now, she seeks [Solitude] a good deal.
translation: Ora, bab miskin, aku wedi dheweke duwe kuatir dhewe saiki, dheweke nggoleki [Solitude] menehi hasil apik.

sentances: Then he would burst rudely into my [Solitude] and while I sopped cold water over his injured members, he would blubber.
translation: Banjur dheweke bakal bledosan rudely menyang [Solitude] lan nalika aku sopped banyu kadhemen liwat anggota tatu, kang bakal blubber.

sentances: There was Radim Palouš, the [Sonorous] philosophical godfather of Kampademia.
translation: Ana Radim Palouš, bapak baptis [Sonorous] filosofis Kampademia.

sentances: At the end, the [Sonorous] Welles concludes with a little talk about Halloween.
translation: Ing pungkasan, [Sonorous] Welles rampung kanthi ngobrol babagan Halloween.

sentances: Franklin Roosevelt's addresses in 1933 and 1937 remain alive, as does the [Sonorous] rhetoric of John F. Kennedy's address in 1961.
translation: Alamat Franklin Roosevelt ing taun 1933 lan 1937 tetep urip, uga retorika [Sonorous] pidato John F. Kennedy ing taun 1961.

sentances: The ancient cities, the dreamy harbors, the [Sonorous] street names that no longer existed.
translation: Kutha kuna, pelabuhan ngimpi, jeneng dalan [Sonorous] sing wis ora ana maneh.

sentances: In my youth, you heard, side-by-side, the church bells ringing and the beautiful, [Sonorous] call to prayer of the muezzin.
translation: Nalika isih enom, sampeyan krungu, sisih-by-side, lonceng pasamuwan muni lan ayu, [Sonorous] adzan saka muazin.

sentances: Her glance wandered from his face away toward the Gulf, whose [Sonorous] murmur reached her like a loving but imperative entreaty.
translation: Mirit dheweke ngumbara saka pasuryan adoh menyang Teluk, kang [Sonorous] murmur tekan dheweke kaya entreaty maha nanging imperatif.

sentances: Pausing at the threshold before opening the door, the [Sonorous] mumble sounding through the deal panels misled me.
translation: Ngaso ing ambang sadurunge mbukak lawang, mumble [Sonorous] muni liwat panel deal mblusukake kula.

sentances: Jerry hit the instrument as he spoke and drowned his own voice in its [Sonorous] roar.
translation: Jerry mencet instrument nalika ngandika lan klelep swara dhewe ing sawijining [Sonorous] nggero.

sentances: Over me, away off, as if from the heavens, I heard a [Sonorous] rumble of mystery words.
translation: Ing sadhuwure aku, adoh, kaya-kaya saka swarga, aku krungu swara misterius [Sonorous].

sentances: I should think 'twould make a splendid subject—you could use such [Sonorous], resounding words.
translation: Aku kudu mikir 'bakal nggawe subyek apik-sampeyan bisa nggunakake kuwi [Sonorous], resounding tembung.

sentances: Lunch finally arrives, this time not a [Sumptuous] feast but fish wrapped in a military newspaper distributed on U.S. bases.
translation: Nedha awan pungkasane teka, wektu iki dudu pesta [Sumptuous] nanging iwak sing dibungkus koran militer sing disebar ing pangkalan AS.

sentances: The table was set with the Cavendish silver and crystal and various [Sumptuous]-looking bottles from the wine cellar.
translation: Tabel iki disetel karo salaka Cavendish lan kristal lan macem-macem [Sumptuous]-looking gendul saka rong anggur.

sentances: “[Sumptuous],” Huston continued, pointing out the image of a richly crimson carriage interior.
translation: "[Sumptuous]," Huston terus, nuduhake gambar interior kreta layung sugih.

sentances: Apple has long been known for luring the best talent the tech world can offer to its [Sumptuous] Cupertino headquarters.
translation: Apple wis suwe dikenal amarga narik bakat paling apik sing bisa ditawakake jagad teknologi menyang markas [Sumptuous] Cupertino.

sentances: People like [Sumptuous] things, and will pay to have them, especially when the copies lack the look and feel of the original.
translation: Wong kaya [Sumptuous] iku, lan bakal mbayar kanggo duwe, utamané nalika salinan lack dipikir lan aran asli.

sentances: The startled guests filed hastily across to find a dainty but [Sumptuous] repast served at little tables.
translation: Tamu-tamu sing kaget banjur cepet-cepet nyabrang golek jajanan sing enak nanging [Sumptuous] sing disuguhake ing meja cilik.

sentances: In the [Sumptuous] dining-room, their elbows on the table, full of meat and drink, they planned and discussed.
translation: Ing ruang makan [Sumptuous], sikut ing meja, kebak daging lan ombenan, padha ngrancang lan ngrembug.

sentances: And the baroness threw a furtive look on the ancient and [Sumptuous] clock in a corner of the room.
translation: Lan baroness mbuwang dipikir furtive ing kuna lan [Sumptuous] jam ing sudhut kamar.

sentances: The autumn was unusually fine, and the colours [Sumptuous] beyond description.
translation: Musim gugur pancen apik banget, lan warna-warna [Sumptuous] ora bisa digambarake.

sentances: Far up against Dalgrothe Mountain appeared a [Sumptuous] star, mystical and red.
translation: Adoh munggah marang Dalgrothe Mountain katon lintang [Sumptuous], mistik lan abang.

sentances: Last month I turned and faced their [Surreptitious] security: “Catch any thieves today?”
translation: Sasi kepungkur aku noleh lan ngadhepi keamanan [Surreptitious]: "Nyekel maling dina iki?"

sentances: Stephanie often takes [Surreptitious] photographs of fellow commuters for a not-yet-realized blog.
translation: Stephanie asring njupuk foto [Surreptitious] kanca-kanca komuter kanggo blog sing durung diwujudake.

sentances: They refused until they had “achieved their [Surreptitious] climax.”
translation: Dheweke nolak nganti "ngrambah klimaks [Surreptitious]".

sentances: But by 1953, with McCarthyism and the second Red Scare in full swing, the FBI moved from [Surreptitious] research to direct contact.
translation: Nanging ing taun 1953, kanthi McCarthyism lan Red Scare kaping pindho ing ayunan lengkap, FBI pindhah saka riset [Surreptitious] menyang kontak langsung.

sentances: Grandmother Penny and Mr. Spackles went to the circus in a more or less [Surreptitious] manner.
translation: Mbah Penny lan Pak Spackles tindak menyang sirkus kanthi cara sing kurang luwih [Surreptitious].

sentances: The house was but a small one, with no [Surreptitious] closets or cupboards, or other hiding-places.
translation: Omah iki mung cilik, ora ana lemari utawa lemari, utawa papan ndhelik liyane.

sentances: She took a [Surreptitious] glance at the profile of Captain Goritz.
translation: Dheweke ndeleng [Surreptitious] ing profil Kapten Goritz.

sentances: It was his first [Surreptitious] taste of fame on the Atlantic coast, and not without its delight.
translation: Iku pisanan [Surreptitious] rasa fame ing pesisir Atlantik, lan ora tanpa bungahaken.

sentances: She reflected quickly that he could not have known anything of her [Surreptitious] trading with the peddler.
translation: Dheweke cepet-cepet mikir yen dheweke ora ngerti apa-apa babagan perdagangan dheweke [Surreptitious] karo tukang dagang.

sentances: But relative to centuries past, America is a marvel of domestic [Tranquility].
translation: Nanging relatif kanggo abad kepungkur, Amerika minangka keajaiban domestik [Tranquility].

sentances: But the illusions of peace and [Tranquility] soon crumble around them like a patch of freshly laid snow.
translation: Nanging khayalan katentreman lan [Tranquility] enggal-enggal ambruk ing saubengé kaya salju salju sing anyar.

sentances: The waiting room is ill-kempt, but inside its institutional blue and white walls, there is a surprising sense of [Tranquility].
translation: Ruang tunggu ora rapi, nanging ing njero tembok biru lan putih institusional, ana rasa kaget [Tranquility].

sentances: “It gives me [Tranquility],” said Batya Katzir, another Ashdod resident.
translation: "Iki menehi kula [Tranquility]," ujare Batya Katzir, warga Ashdod liyane.

sentances: So it was something that would symbolize some [Tranquility], peace—anything that would give it a good energy.
translation: Dadi ana sing bakal nglambangake sawetara [Tranquility], tentrem-apa wae sing bakal menehi energi sing apik.

sentances: In your last letter you ask whether your remaining at Bath is necessary to my [Tranquility].
translation: Ing layang pungkasan sampeyan takon apa sampeyan isih ana ing Bath perlu kanggo [Tranquility].

sentances: The public [Tranquility] had not been disturbed, when armed peasants introduced themselves.
translation: Umum [Tranquility] wis ora kaganggu, nalika petani bersenjata ngenalaken piyambak.

sentances: Who was this mysterious correspondent that dared to disturb the [Tranquility] of his retreat?
translation: Sapa wartawan misterius iki sing wani ngganggu [Tranquility] mundur?

sentances: He did so with the greatest [Tranquility], as if the objection was the most insignificant affair in the world.
translation: Dheweke nindakake kanthi [Tranquility] sing paling gedhe, kaya-kaya bantahan kasebut minangka urusan sing paling ora penting ing donya.

sentances: I am obliged to write in haste, and very imperfectly, a work which requires the leisure and [Tranquility] I do not enjoy.
translation: Aku kapekso kanggo nulis kanthi cepet, lan banget ora sampurna, karya sing mbutuhake luang lan [Tranquility] aku ora seneng.

sentances: And that means they also fall under the [Umbrella] of programs most likely to get the axe when state and federal budgets are tight.
translation: Lan tegese padha uga tiba ing [Payung] program paling kamungkinan kanggo njaluk kapak nalika negara lan Federal budget nyenyet.

sentances: The program—weirdly—is now under the [Umbrella] of ABC News, and is suffering from flat ratings and an aging demographic.
translation: Program-aneh-saiki ana ing [Payung] saka ABC News, lan gerah saka ratings flat lan demografi tuwa.

sentances: The law professor, Benny Tai, urged the students to “retreat and take the spirit of the [Umbrella] Movement into the community.”
translation: Profesor hukum, Benny Tai, ngajak para siswa supaya "mundur lan njupuk semangat Gerakan [Payung] menyang komunitas."

sentances: Think of them as the Monuments Men and Women of the [Umbrella] Movement.
translation: Coba wong-wong mau minangka Monumen Pria lan Wanita saka Gerakan [Payung].

sentances: From Carnations to [Umbrella], the history and importance of names people give to nonviolent movements.
translation: Saka Carnations kanggo [Payung], sajarah lan pentinge jeneng wong menehi kanggo gerakan non-kekerasan.

sentances: She looked up in his face, leaning on his arm beneath the encircling shadow of the [Umbrella] which he had lifted.
translation: Dheweke katon munggah ing pasuryan, condong ing lengen ing sangisore bayangan encircling saka [Payung] kang wis diangkat.

sentances: Now that it rains there's no more room under your [Umbrella] than there was a few moments ago, when the sun was shining.
translation: Saiki wis udan ora ana papan liyane ing ngisor [Payung] sampeyan tinimbang sawetara wektu kepungkur, nalika srengenge wis sumunar.

sentances: As he spoke he wedged himself between Grandfather Mole and the stem of the toadstool [Umbrella].
translation: Nalika ngandika dheweke wedged piyambak antarane Eyang Mole lan gagang toadstool [Payung].

sentances: "It's plain that your [Umbrella] didn't grow as much as you thought," Mr. Meadow Mouse retorted.
translation: "Jelas yen [Payungmu] ora tuwuh kaya sing dikira," wangsulane Pak Meadow Mouse.

sentances: He put on his big straw hat, and taking his [Umbrella] from the stand in the hall, followed the lady in black, never overtaking her.
translation: Dheweke nganggo topi jerami sing gedhe, lan njupuk [Payung] saka papan ing bale, ngetutake wanita sing nganggo ireng, ora nate nyusul.

sentances: These are seriously fun journeys that allow users to satisfy their [Wanderlust] without a plane ticket.
translation: Iki minangka perjalanan sing nyenengake banget sing ngidini pangguna bisa marem [Wanderlust] tanpa tiket pesawat.

sentances: [Wanderlust] stresses a no-harm-done mantra, and their intention is not, as Austin puts it, “to poke holes in the security theater.”
translation: [Wanderlust] nandheske mantra sing ora ana gunane, lan tujuane ora, kaya sing dikandhakake Austin, "kanggo nggawe bolongan ing teater keamanan."

sentances: With the watch, [Wanderlust] found a way to cover costs and ensure a varied and trustworthy clientele.
translation: Kanthi jam tangan, [Wanderlust] nemokake cara kanggo nutupi biaya lan njamin klien sing maneka warna lan bisa dipercaya.

sentances: The Night Heron was the first adventure [Wanderlust] opened up to an audience larger than a pre-set guest list.
translation: The Night Heron minangka petualangan pisanan [Wanderlust] dibukak kanggo pamirsa sing luwih gedhe tinimbang dhaptar tamu sing wis disetel.

sentances: The [Wanderlust] Projects duo are building bars in water towers and romantic getaways in abandoned resorts.
translation: Duo [Wanderlust] Projects mbangun bar ing menara banyu lan liburan romantis ing resor sing ditinggalake.

sentances: Easy as life was for Gorky in this city, where he remained for a while, the "[Wanderlust]" again seized him.
translation: Gampang kaya urip Gorky ing kutha iki, ing ngendi dheweke tetep sawetara wektu, "[Wanderlust]" maneh nyekel dheweke.

sentances: He was a boyish and attractive individual whom the [Wanderlust] had driven westward from his home in Wisconsin.
translation: Dheweke minangka bocah lanang lan atraktif sing diusir [Wanderlust] menyang kulon saka omahe ing Wisconsin.

sentances: The [Wanderlust] becomes chronic, and mainly because it was not treated properly in its intermittent stage.
translation: [Wanderlust] dadi kronis, lan utamane amarga ora diobati kanthi bener ing tahap intermiten.

sentances: The sweet fragrance of blossoming orchards tingled in your nostrils and thrilled you with [Wanderlust].
translation: Arum manis saka kebon kembang sing mekar ing irungmu lan nyenengake sampeyan [Wanderlust].

sentances: Moonlight nights had come and the [Wanderlust] was growing more and more insistent in his veins.
translation: Wengi padhang rembulan wis teka lan [Wanderlust] saya tambah ngeyel ing urat.

sentances: Somebody maybe doesn't have the [Wherewithal] to get out, the means to get out—I had that.
translation: Mungkin ana wong sing ora duwe [Wherewithal] kanggo metu, sarana kanggo metu-aku duwe.

sentances: I lack the [Wherewithal] to start my own competing certifying board, to say nothing of the chutzpah.
translation: Aku lack [Wherewithal] kanggo miwiti Papan sertifikat saingan dhewe, kanggo ngomong apa-apa saka chutzpah.

sentances: Those who have the [Wherewithal] to shop online with greater ease and frequency have a greater ability to avoid sales taxes.
translation: Sing duwe [Wherewithal] kanggo toko online kanthi luwih gampang lan frekuensi duwe kemampuan sing luwih gedhe kanggo nyegah pajak dodolan.

sentances: The British middle class no longer had servants--but they also lacked the [Wherewithal] to obtain fancy new appliances.
translation: Kelas menengah Inggris ora duwe abdi maneh - nanging uga ora duwe [Wherewithal] kanggo entuk peralatan anyar sing apik.

sentances: “Even if you had the [Wherewithal] to embarrass a reporter, there was no mechanism to do it,” Mr. Cramer said.
translation: "Sanajan sampeyan duwe [Wherewithal] kanggo ngisin-isini wartawan, ora ana mekanisme kanggo nindakake," ujare Pak Cramer.

sentances: But a lawyer who needed the [Wherewithal] finally condescended to risk the task, and into it he plunged.
translation: Nanging pengacara sing mbutuhake [Wherewithal] pungkasane ngakoni risiko tugas kasebut, lan dheweke terjun.

sentances: Secondly, we had already been for some time at work to fix up the [Wherewithal] to meet our chronic nightmare, the water trouble.
translation: Kapindho, kita wis sawetara wektu ing karya kanggo ndandani [Wherewithal] kanggo ketemu ngipi elek kronis kita, masalah banyu.

sentances: And how do you know that I have got [Wherewithal] to pay the reckoning?
translation: Lan kepiye sampeyan ngerti yen aku kudu mbayar pitungan?

sentances: If they have [Wherewithal] to persuade the Jury to bring it in Manslaughter, what are they the worse for it?
translation: Yen dheweke duwe [Wherewithal] kanggo mbujuk Juri kanggo nggawa ing Manslaughter, apa sing luwih ala kanggo iku?

sentances: He immediately clamored for the [Wherewithal] to fill an aching void that was making itself painfully felt in his midsection.
translation: Dheweke langsung njaluk [Wherewithal] kanggo ngisi kekosongan sing lara sing nyebabake rasa lara ing bagian tengah.

sentances: But the words “responsible” and “Republican” are no longer typeable together except in moods of mockery, or at least [Wistfulness].
translation: Nanging tembung "tanggung jawab" lan "Republikan" ora bisa diketik maneh kajaba ing swasana moyoki, utawa paling ora [Wistfulness].

sentances: That gave last night's dinner with Ahmadinejad an air of [Wistfulness] tinged with growing fear.
translation: Sing menehi nedha bengi bengi karo Ahmadinejad hawa [Wistfulness] tinged karo tambah wedi.

sentances: Winston smiled, though there was a [Wistfulness] in his eyes as he saw the faint bewilderment in his companions' faces.
translation: Winston mesem, sanajan ana [Wistfulness] ing mripate nalika dheweke weruh bewilderment Samar ing pasuryan kanca kang.

sentances: For at least five minutes he stood without moving, his whole face softened into a boyish [Wistfulness].
translation: Paling ora limang menit dheweke ngadeg tanpa obah, kabeh pasuryane dadi cah lanang [Wistfulness].

sentances: She rose at this, turning her eyes about the room as if from the extremity of martyrdom or the [Wistfulness] of some deep thought.
translation: Dheweke wungu ing iki, ngowahi mripate babagan kamar kaya-kaya saka extremity martir utawa [Wistfulness] sawetara pikiran jero.

sentances: She always suggested tea before the hour, and her friend always, but with so different a [Wistfulness], rang for it.
translation: Dheweke tansah disaranake teh sadurunge jam, lan kancane tansah, nanging karo supaya beda [Wistfulness], rang kanggo iku.

sentances: I was awake at once––wide awake for him: moved by the [Wistfulness] of this appeal to some perception of his need.
translation: Aku langsung tangi––awake kanggo dheweke: dipindhah dening [Wistfulness] banding iki kanggo sawetara pemahaman kabutuhan.

sentances: Who was the most erotic poet of the late Renaissance and early Baroque, when the quatrain reached its courtly [Zenith]?
translation: Sapa pujangga paling erotis ing pungkasan Renaissance lan awal Baroque, nalika quatrain tekan courtly [Zenith]?

sentances: This reached its [Zenith] when he and Jon Stewart held their Rally to Restore Sanity And/Or Fear in 2010.
translation: Iki tekan [Zenith] nalika dheweke lan Jon Stewart nganakake Rally kanggo Mulihake Sanity lan / Utawa Wedi ing 2010.

sentances: In his own mind he is at the [Zenith] of his life, a man in full.
translation: Ing pikirane dhewe dheweke ana ing [Zenith] uripe, wong kanthi lengkap.

sentances: The major labor unions - then at the [Zenith] of their political power - disliked Johnson.
translation: Serikat buruh utama - banjur ing [Zenith] kekuwatan politike - ora seneng karo Johnson.

sentances: In 1986, at the [Zenith] of her strength, that figure was reduced to 1.9 million.
translation: Ing taun 1986, ing [Zenith] kekuwatane, angka kasebut suda dadi 1,9 yuta.

sentances: The sky was alight from [Zenith] to horizon, the Nile aflame with sunrise, by the time the letter was written.
translation: Awang-awang saka [Zenith] nganti tekan ing cakrawala, Kali Nil murub ing srengenge, nalika layang kasebut ditulis.

sentances: The leathered Diapason, indeed, is now attaining a [Zenith] of popularity both in England and America.
translation: The Diapason leathered, tenan, saiki entuk [Zenith] popularitas loro ing Inggris lan Amerika.

sentances: Coloured shafts mapped the vault from horizon to [Zenith] like the spokes of a prodigious wheel of fire.
translation: Shafts colored map vault saka cakrawala kanggo [Zenith] kaya spokes saka rodha geni prodigious.

sentances: The sun, a ball of fiery brass, burned directly in the [Zenith], so that the shadow of the foliage lay like a carpet about her feet.
translation: Srengenge, werni saka kuningan murub, burned langsung ing [Zenith], supaya bayangan saka godhong-godhongan enom lay kaya karpet ing sikil.

sentances: How did it fare with the poor all over Europe in the centuries when Christianity was at the [Zenith] of its power?
translation: Piyé carané wong-wong miskin ing saindhenging Eropah ing abad-abad nalika Kristen ana ing [Zenith] kekuwatane?
